@CreatorAlex wrote:

I’ll just say first of all, ::object will only make temporary objects show up. Unless the command writes to your source, that is.

Since I don’t have a 602 to look at atm, I couldn’t tell you where in the source to add objects. (I do remember it wasn’t very obvious where they went)
